results.name: X Ghosted.3 IN J 'Shock Pink'
results.story: An indoor soccer shoe made for kids, the adidas X Ghosted.3 IN J ‘Shock Pink’ features a highlighter finish designed to stand out on the pitch. The sock-like upper is constructed from coated mesh and equipped with a low-cut collar that wraps around the ankle without compromising mobility. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length EVA midsole, reinforced by a grippy gum rubber outsole that offers superior traction on indoor surfaces.

results.name: Wmns Chuck Taylor All Star High 'Camo'
results.story: The Converse women’s Chuck Taylor All Star High ‘Camo’ layers on multiple archive prints on a sustainable build. Leopard-print laces secure a 100% recycled poly-canvas upper, covered in a brown and green camo print and translucent zebra stripes. Additional leopard spots land on the sneaker’s heel overlay. The high-top rests on an off-white rubber midsole, supported underfoot by a standard Chuck outsole in brown rubber.

results.name: Chuck Taylor All Star Low 'Dramatic Nights - Black'
The Simpsons x Superstar 'Squishee'
results.story: Launching as part of a larger collection with the long-running animated series, The Simpsons x adidas Superstar 'Squishee' takes inspiration from the frozen beverage offered at Springfield’s Kwik-E-Mart. Bold black lines are applied to the lime green synthetic leather upper, accented with an oval-shaped insert on the lateral quarter panel. Orange serrated three-stripes are matched by a heel tab marked with adidas’ Trefoil logo. Additional branding hits include a Squishee lace jewel and a woven Kwik-E-Mart tag atop the transparent tongue. A semi-translucent rubber cupsole anchors the low-top.

results.name: Wmns Chuck Taylor All Star Platform High 'Vintage Floral'
results.story: The Converse women’s Chuck Taylor All Star Platform High ‘Vintage Floral’ transforms the foundational sneaker with a summer-ready all-over print and a retooled design. The high-top carries a traditional canvas upper entirely covered in pink, crimson and orange blossoms. The ornate pattern is offset by a reinforced rubber toe cap and platform midsole, both rendered in a subtle off-white finish. A diamond-tread brown rubber outsole offers durable traction underfoot.

adidas Ultra Boost 6.0 Crew Blue
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost 6.0 ‘Crew Blue’ affirms the German sportswear brand’s commitment to sustainability and the reduction of plastic waste. Indigo fibers are woven into an off-white Primeknit upper that incorporates Parley Ocean Plastic, while the molded midfoot cage and heel counter are made with recycled fishing nets. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a Stretchweb outsole built with Continental rubber.

Dime x Skate Mid Skool LTD 'Off White'
results.story: The Dime x Vans Skate Mid Skool LTD ‘Off White’ delivers a simple two-tone colorway of the retro silhouette. White nylon is utilized on the upper, reinforced with tonal suede overlays and accented with a stitched side stripe. The Montreal-based skate brand leaves its mark on the purple leather heel tab and co-branded woven tongue tag. Performance benefits on the skate-ready build include a protective DURACAP underlay and an ULTRACUSH polyurethane sockliner. Underfoot, the translucent outsole reveals an oversized Dime logo.

UltraBoost 21 Primeblue 'Non Dyed'
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost 21 Primeblue ‘Non Dyed’ combines lightweight performance with a sustainable build. Designed to hug the unique contours of the foot, the undyed Primeknit upper is constructed in part with recycled Parley Ocean Plastic and zero virgin polyester. The sneaker’s supportive heel counter and midfoot cage maintain the blank-canvas aesthetic. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, enhanced with adidas’ LEP Torsion System for increased energy return.

Nike Air Max 95 NRG LeBron Lakers
results.story: The LeBron James x Nike Air Max 95 NRG ‘Lakers’ delivers a special-edition colorway of the sneaker that the NBA icon counts as one of his favorites. The left shoe features a yellow suede upper with contrasting purple accents, while the converse is featured on the right. LeBron’s personal logo replaces traditional Air Max branding atop the tongue. Underfoot, the semi-translucent rubber outsole lists some of LeBron’s many career milestones, as well as his 23 jersey number across the right and left shoe.

Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Marathon'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from the Indianapolis 500 and the event’s iconic racing suit designs, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘Marathon’ features an energetic blend of colors throughout the breathable textile upper. Russell Westbrook’s personal logo is embroidered on the tongue, while a checkerboard overlay adds an additional motorsport flourish. The lightweight build is supported by a lightweight Phylon midsole with a TPU shank and double-stacked Zoom Air units in the forefoot.

UltraBoost DNA CC_1 'Legend Ink Gradient'
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost DNA CC_1 ‘Legend Ink Gradient’ showcases a monochromatic finish on a running shoe that borrows cooling technology from the brand’s retro Climacool line. Aerodynamic air channels are built into the blacked-out Primeknit upper, made in part with recycled Parley Ocean Plastic and zero virgin polyester. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, rendered in a color-fade effect and supported by a Stretchweb Continental rubber outsole. Classic Climacool branding adorns the tongue.
